summary: This is a travel voucher approval notification for a DOJ trip related to the Epstein investigation. The voucher covers expenses for a witness interview trip to Pensacola, FL in February 2020, indicating ongoing investigative activity after Epstein's death.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip - Pensacola
events.description: DOJ personnel traveled to Pensacola, FL for witness interviews related to the Epstein investigation

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Completion
events.description: Completion of witness interview trip to Pensacola, FL for Epstein investigation

keyFacts: The DOJ was conducting witness interviews for the Epstein investigation in February 2020, months after Epstein's death in August 2019
A travel voucher was approved for trip ID 11062816 with voucher total expenses of $1,040.52
The trip purpose was specifically identified as 'R20NYS13401 - Epstein Investigation - Witness interview'
The document shows ongoing investigative activity by the DOJ related to the Epstein case in early 2020
The travel was to Pensacola, FL for witness interviews from February 19-20, 2020
